Upon visiting a restaurant:

Frontend sends the restaurant info to the backend
Backend reads the user and restaurant info (name, opening hours, and location)
If the restaurant already exists, find that restaurant and retrieve restaurant id
    - check congruence of data
    - if incongruent, check similar data (restaurant name is constant, as is location, hours could change)
if no restaurant, create new restaurant, keep track of generated restaurant id
Create new row in UserDinedRestaurants with user_id and restaurant_ids
Return 200 when successful, return 500 if failed
